# Project Structure & Organization

## Workspace Overview

This is an Angular 20 UI library workspace called `ngx-nova-ui` with signal-based architecture and standalone components.

## Key Directories

- **Library Source**: [projects/ngx-nova-ui/src/](mdc:projects/ngx-nova-ui/src/)
- **Public API**: [projects/ngx-nova-ui/src/public-api.ts](mdc:projects/ngx-nova-ui/src/public-api.ts) - All public exports
- **Components**: [projects/ngx-nova-ui/src/lib/components/](mdc:projects/ngx-nova-ui/src/lib/components/) - Component implementations
- **Services**: [projects/ngx-nova-ui/src/lib/services/](mdc:projects/ngx-nova-ui/src/lib/services/) - Shared services
- **Styles**: [projects/ngx-nova-ui/src/lib/styles/](mdc:projects/ngx-nova-ui/src/lib/styles/) - Global CSS and theme variables
- **Storybook**: [projects/ngx-nova-ui/.storybook/](mdc:projects/ngx-nova-ui/.storybook/) - Storybook configuration
- **Build Output**: [dist/ngx-nova-ui/](mdc:dist/ngx-nova-ui/) - Compiled library

## Component Structure Pattern

Each component follows this structure:

```
components/<name>/
├── <name>.ts          # Component implementation
├── <name>.html        # Template (if external)
├── <name>.scss        # Component styles
├── <name>.stories.ts  # Storybook stories
└── index.ts           # Public exports
```

## Configuration Files

- **Workspace Config**: [angular.json](mdc:angular.json) - Angular workspace configuration
- **Library Config**: [projects/ngx-nova-ui/ng-package.json](mdc:projects/ngx-nova-ui/ng-package.json) - Library packaging
- **TypeScript**: [projects/ngx-nova-ui/tsconfig.lib.json](mdc:projects/ngx-nova-ui/tsconfig.lib.json) - Library TypeScript config
- **ESLint**: [eslint.config.js](mdc:eslint.config.js) - Code quality rules
- **Prettier**: [.prettierrc.json](mdc:.prettierrc.json) - Code formatting

## Naming Conventions

- **Selectors**: Element selectors prefixed `nova-` (kebab-case), directive selectors `nova` (camelCase)
- **Filenames**: Angular 20 style (e.g., `button.ts` not `button.component.ts`)
- **CSS Classes**: Use `nova-` prefix for component classes
- **CSS Variables**: Use `--nova-` prefix for theme variables
